\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9589514 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 Would she have a day off and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16539070 HM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 Oh yes. Yes, she used to have I think - one Sunday off, one Sunday off I think - every third week. Sometimes she\rquote d take us over to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Greenwich{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} to her people. Lived at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Greenwich{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. And - I remember getting a good hiding - when we came home, because she\rquote d taken us somewhere - and we had to go under like a - subway. And in this subway she got us to sing. She\rquote 
s singing this song, all along the rails, and what a lovely game. And when we came home my mother said, have you been good when you\rquote ve been out with Lizzie? I said, yes, and we\rquote ve been singing. My mother said you\rquote 
ve been singing? I said, yes. So she called Lizzie. She said, the children been singing? So she said, yes. She said, well don\rquote t teach my children to sing in the street. See? Yes. I remember that song plain.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9589514 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 Did she used to eat with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16539070 HM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 Oh yes. Yes, yes. She -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9589514 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 Was she a young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16539070 HM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 Oh yes, she was only young, yes. And you know - you - 
you talk about memories, I was getting my little boy home from school - on one occasion, one - the elder one used to go to another school, he was capable of coming home on his own, and - coming home - coming up the street, I just got to my door - and some
body called my name. And my Lesley said to me, mummy, someone\rquote s calling you. So I looked across the road. I said, well I don\rquote t know who it is. So she said, you are, Hannah aren\rquote 
t you? I said, yes. She came over. I said, Lizzie Cable? That was her surname.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9589514 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3412272\charrsid6362028 How long was that since you\rquote d last seen her?
